SIMPLE: parsonage
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Parsonage
<hw>Par"son*age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Eng.
Eccl. Law)</fld> <def>A certain portion of lands, tithes, and offerings,
for the maintenance of the parson of a parish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The glebe and house, or the house only, owned by a
parish or ecclesiastical society, and appropriated to the maintenance or
use of the incumbent or settled pastor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Money paid for the support of a parson.</def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What have I been paying stipend and teind, <qex>parsonage</qex>
and vicarage, for?</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parsoned</ent>⟦br⟧
